 for divisions, which examines the appraisal outcomes for two divisions using both ROI and RI.\"\"\",11\n260,\"\"\"RETURN ON INVESTMENT (ROI)\"\"\",\"\"\"ASSESSING DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS AT A MANUFACTURING COMPANY\"\"\",\"\"\"The case of Assessing Divisional Performance and Investment Decisions at a Manufacturing Company involves calculating the ROI for Divisions B and C.\"\"\",10\n1181,\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME\"\"\",\"\"\"ASSESSING DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS AT A MANUFACTURING COMPANY\"\"\",\"\"\"The case of Assessing Divisional Performance and Investment Decisions at a Manufacturing Company involves calculating the residual income for Divisions B and C.\"\"\",10\n1042,\"\"\"RETURN ON CAPITAL EMPLOYED (ROCE)\"\"\",\"\"\"CAPITAL EMPLOYED\"\"\",\"\"\"Return on capital employed (ROCE) uses Capital employed in its calculation.\"\"\",10\n74,\"\"\"CUSTOMER SERVICE\"\"\",\"\"\"CUSTOMER RELATIONSHIP MANAGEMENT SYSTEM (CRM)\"\"\",\"\"\"A CRM system aims to improve customer service.\"\"\",10\n1168,\"\"\"ROI\"\"\",\"\"\"PROPOSAL 2\"\"\",\"\"\"Proposal 2 increases the divisional ROI, which could lead to the divisional manager accepting it despite it being not acceptable to the company.\"\"\",10\n1167,\"\"\"QUIZ: ROI AND RESIDUAL INCOME\"\"\",\"\"\"ROI\"\"\",\"\"\"The quiz involves calculating the current ROI and residual income for Division X and showing how they would change under two proposals.\"\"\",10\n1171,\"\"\"ROI\"\"\",\"\"\"QUIZ: ROI CALCULATION FOR DAMON CO\u2019S DIVISIONS\"\"\",\"\"\"The concept of ROI is related to the quiz on ROI calculation for Damon Co\u2019s divisions, which involves calculating the ROI based on provided financial information.\"\"\",10\n1163,\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME (RI)\"\"\",\"\"\"QUIZ: ROI VS. RESIDUAL INCOME\"\"\",\"\"\"The concept of Residual Income (RI) is directly related to the quiz on ROI vs. Residual Income, which compares decision-making using ROI and RI.\"\"\",10\n1159,\"\"\"ADVANTAGES OF ROI\"\"\",\"\"\"ROI\"\"\",\"\"\"Advantages of ROI include ease of comparison between divisions, focus on scarce capital resources, encouragement of reduction in non-essential investment, and easily understood percentages.\"\"\",9\n1182,\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME\"\"\",\"\"\"CONTROLLABLE PROFIT\"\"\",\"\"\"Residual income is calculated using controllable profit, subtracting the imputed interest on capital employed.\"\"\",9\n79,\"\"\"SALES GROWTH\"\"\",\"\"\"CUSTOMER RELATIONSHIP MANAGEMENT SYSTEM (CRM)\"\"\",\"\"\"A CRM system drives sales growth.\"\"\",9\n1160,\"\"\"DISADVANTAGES OF ROI\"\"\",\"\"\"ROI\"\"\",\"\"\"Disadvantages of ROI include the risk of dysfunctional decision-making, subjective definition of capital employed, potential increase in ROI over time due to depreciation, and risk of window-dressing.\"\"\",9\n1443,\"\"\"NON-FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE INDICATORS\"\"\",\"\"\"EVALUATING PERFORMANCE AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS AT WELCO\"\"\",\"\"\"The case of Evaluating Performance and Investment Decisions at Welco discusses the potential introduction of Non-financial performance indicators to improve long-term performance.\"\"\",9\n1043,\"\"\"RETURN ON CAPITAL EMPLOYED (ROCE)\"\"\",\"\"\"OPERATING PROFIT MARGIN\"\"\",\"\"\"Return on Capital Employed (ROCE)\"\" and \"\"Operating Profit Margin\"\" are financial performance metrics used to evaluate a company's profitability and efficiency. ROCE is calculated using the Operating Profit Margin, indicating a direct relationship between these two metrics.\",9\n264,\"\"\"RETURN ON INVESTMENT (ROI)\"\"\",\"\"\"PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS: IMPLEMENTING THE BALANCED SCORECARD AND RESIDUAL INCOME APPROACHES\"\"\",\"\"\"The case of Performance Measurement and Investment Decisions: Implementing the Balanced Scorecard and Residual Income Approaches involves calculating Return on investment (ROI) for two divisions.\"\"\",9\n1165,\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME (RI)\"\"\",\"\"\"PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS: IMPLEMENTING THE BALANCED SCORECARD AND RESIDUAL INCOME APPROACHES\"\"\",\"\"\"The case of Performance Measurement and Investment Decisions: Implementing the Balanced Scorecard and Residual Income Approaches involves calculating Residual income (RI) for two divisions.\"\"\",9\n1164,\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME (RI)\"\"\",\"\"\"QUIZ: ROI AND RI FOR DIVISIONS\"\"\",\"\"\"The concept of Residual Income (RI) is related to the quiz on ROI and RI for divisions, which examines the appraisal outcomes for two divisions using both ROI and RI.\"\"\",9\n1040,\"\"\"RETURN ON EQUITY (ROE)\"\"\",\"\"\"CAPITAL EMPLOYED\"\"\",\"\"\"Return on equity (ROE) is related to Capital employed as it uses equity components in its calculation.\"\"\",8\n1736,\"\"\"OPERATING PROFIT MARGIN\"\"\",\"\"\"EVALUATING PERFORMANCE AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS AT WELCO\"\"\",\"\"\"The case of Evaluating Performance and Investment Decisions at Welco involves analyzing the Operating profit margin for both the Design and Gearbox divisions.\"\"\",8\n1166,\"\"\"IMPUTED INTEREST\"\"\",\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME\"\"\",\"\"\"Imputed interest is subtracted from controllable profit to calculate residual income.\"\"\",8\n1161,\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME (RI)\"\"\",\"\"\"IMPUTED INTEREST\"\"\",\"\"\"Residual income (RI) is calculated by deducting imputed interest from pre-tax profit.\"\"\",8\n1162,\"\"\"RESIDUAL INCOME (RI)\"\"\",\"\"\"QUIZ: ROI AND RESIDUAL INCOME\"\"\",\"\"\"The quiz involves calculating the current ROI and residual income for Division X and showing how they would change under two proposals.\"\"\",8\n1044,\"\"\"RETURN ON CAPITAL EMPLOYED (ROCE)\"\"\",\"\"\"ASSET TURNOVER RATIO\"\"\",\"\"\"Return on capital employed (ROCE) is calculated using the Asset turnover ratio.\"\"\",7\n1045,\"\"\"CAPITAL EMPLOYED\"\"\",\"\"\"NON-CURRENT ASSETS\"\"\",\"\"\"Non-current assets are a component of capital employed, representing long-term investments used to generate profits.\"\"\",7\n1046,\"\"\"CAPITAL EMPLOYED\"\"\",\"\"\"INVENTORY AN